<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-012-898  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 012 898.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Soft-Letter  Dec 26 1989 v7 n13 p6(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT The Mercury Group 1989.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Microsoft. (William H. Gates on small size of Macintosh market)andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT/><TEXT>MICROSOFT MICROSOFT chairman Bill Gates on why the relatively small size ofthe Macintosh market isn't a drawback: &quot;We get dramatically more [sales] forevery Macintosh that's sold than we get for every PC.andP;  It's over four timesas much.andP;  Frankly, even if half as many Macs were selling it would still bevery profitable for me to do all the things we're doing.&quot;andP;  (Qouted inMacintosh News, 10/30/89)</TEXT></DOC>